nathan zuckerman is a fictional character created by the writer philip roth , who uses him as his protagonist and narrator , a type of alter ego , in many of his novels."philip roth 's ' ghost ' returns " , npr , 25 september 2007   character roth first created a character named nathan zuckerman in the novel my life as a man ( 1974 ) , where he is the " product " of another fictional roth figure , the writer peter tarnopol ( making zuckerman , in his original form , an " alter - alter-ego " ) .

books & authors : a writer named nathan zuckerman is featured in several books by this author

philip roth